**GradePredictor**

**Introduction**

This project is a website that allows students to know their expected final grade for their subjects.

**Problem Statement**

Problem: Risk of Losing a Scholarship or Having to Stay for Summer Retakes  
Many students do not keep track of their academic performance. They may believe everything is going well, while in reality, their grades suggest otherwise. Our website solves this problem by helping students understand the grade they are most likely to receive in a given subject.  
By seeing their projected results, students can make informed decisions—whether they can afford to relax or, on the contrary, need to put in more effort to avoid losing their scholarship or having to retake the course in the summer.  
This tool is especially useful for students who work part-time or are actively involved in student life. It helps them stay aware of their academic standing and better balance their academic, professional, and extracurricular commitments.

**Objectives**

To help students better monitor their academic performance and reduce the number of retakes and scholarship losses.

**Technology Stack**

• Frontend: HTML, CSS, Bootstrap, JavaScript

• Backend: Django 4.x , Scikit-learn

• Database: PostgreSQL

• Others: Figma, Docker, docker-compose 

**Installation Instructions**

 Requirements: Docker and docker-compose Git for downloading the code

1. Clone the repository  
2. Create a .env file with necessary settings  
3. Run docker-compose up  
4. A superuser is created automatically  
5. Access the app via browser at http://localhost:8000

**Testing** 

Main Pages of the Website: The main and additional pages were tested to ensure they function correctly for both regular users and administrators.

Form Testing and Prediction Check: We tested the functionality of creating courses, adding students, notifying them about assignments, assigning grades, and, of course, the grade prediction mechanism.  
Accessibility Check: The interface was tested to ensure it displays correctly on mobile devices and across different browsers.

**Known Issues / Limitations (Optional)**

In fact, our website was supposed to take the data of students from the site moodle.sdu.edu.kz. But it was very difficult for us to do this, so we simply decided to create an admin account so that only he would insert the information.
